<author><name><![CDATA[MottZilla]]></name></author>
<updated>2010-03-11T20:22:41-07:00</updated>
<published>2010-03-11T20:22:41-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6149&amp;p=58028#p58028</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6149&amp;p=58028#p58028"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Making a Cart Save Scores that didn't come with a Battery?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6149&amp;p=58028#p58028"><![CDATA[
This can be done but it involves some hacking and assembly language understanding.<br /><br />Basically what you'd want to do is find the point in the game code where High Score entries occur. You'd branch to your own code after this to copy the High Score table into the battery backed RAM. Then you'd need to find the point where the High Score table is normally initialized and replace it with your own code that restores the table from battery backed ram. You'd also want to implement a checksum of some sort to verify that the contents of the battery backup are valid. That way if they are corrupted or if it's the first time loading up it won't load garbage values as the high score table. It also would save you from having to implement a method of clearing the score table.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1726">MottZilla</a> — Thu Mar 11, 2010 8:22 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
